# Normalize line endings to LF in the working tree on every platform.
#
# Why this matters: the generated TypeScript bindings drift check
# (`export_typescript_bindings`) compares the freshly-rendered string against the
# committed `irodori-api.ts` with a raw equality check. On Windows CI, git would
# otherwise check the file out with CRLF (autocrlf), so the raw comparison fails
# even though every line is identical — which broke every release build. Forcing
# LF keeps the committed file byte-identical to the LF-rendered output on Windows,
# macOS, and Linux alike.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets must never be normalized.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.icns binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.parquet binary
*.avro binary
